1️⃣ User Package

Purpose: Manages customers (and admins).

Workflow:

UserController handles HTTP requests like /register or /login.

UserService contains business logic: create user, validate credentials, hash passwords.

UserRepository interacts with the database.

UserMapper converts UserRequest → User entity and User → UserResponse.

Integration: Works with security to authenticate users and generate JWT tokens.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2️⃣ Product Package

Purpose: Handles products and their details.

Workflow:

ProductController provides endpoints like /products, /products/{id}.

ProductService implements business logic: create product, update stock, search/filter.

ProductRepository queries database.

ProductMapper maps between ProductRequest/ProductResponse and Product entity.

Integration: Linked with category (each product belongs to a category), and cart/order (users buy products).
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

3️⃣ Category Package

Purpose: Organizes products.

Workflow:

CategoryController allows CRUD operations for categories.

CategoryService ensures consistent category management.

Products reference a Category entity for filtering/grouping.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

4️⃣ Cart Package

Purpose: Stores products users want to buy temporarily.

Workflow:

CartController handles requests like addToCart, viewCart, removeFromCart.

CartService manages business logic: calculate total, check stock, merge items.

CartRepository persists cart state in the database.

CartMapper converts Cart ↔ CartResponse.

Integration:

Linked to User (one cart per user).

References Product through CartItem.

Checkout triggers creation of an Order.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

5️⃣ Order Package

Purpose: Represents completed or pending purchases.

Workflow:

OrderController handles /orders, /orders/{id} endpoints.

OrderService validates the cart, calculates totals, creates order entries.

OrderRepository persists orders and order items.

OrderMapper converts entities ↔ DTOs for API responses.

Integration:

Connects User → Order

Includes OrderItem → references Product

Connected with Payment for order completion.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

6️⃣ Payment Package

Purpose: Handles payment processing.

Workflow:

PaymentController exposes endpoints like /pay or /payment/{orderId}.

PaymentService implements payment logic: validate amount, update order status.

PaymentRepository saves payment info (amount, method, transaction ID).

PaymentMapper converts entities ↔ DTOs.

Integration:

One-to-one relationship with Order (an order has one payment).

Works with User indirectly for payment ownership.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

8️⃣ Security Package

Purpose: Protects the backend with authentication and authorization.

Workflow:

SecurityConfig defines which endpoints require authentication and which roles can access them.

JwtFilter checks incoming requests for JWT tokens.

JwtService generates and validates tokens.

CustomUserDetailsService loads user credentials for authentication.

Integration:

All controllers can enforce access control.

Ensures only logged-in users can create orders, payments, carts, etc.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

9️⃣ Config Package

Purpose: Global app settings.

Examples:

CorsConfig → allows requests from your frontend.

ModelMapperConfig → global configuration for entity ↔ DTO mapping.

SwaggerConfig → generates API documentation.

Integration: Works across all packages.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔟 Common Package

Purpose: Utilities and exception handling.

Examples:

GlobalExceptionHandler → catches errors like “Product not found” or “Out of stock”.

DateUtil → date formatting for orders/payments.

Integration: Used by services and controllers across all features.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔄 Typical Backend Flow (End-to-End)

User registers/login → UserController + security → JWT token issued

Browse products → ProductController → returns DTOs via ProductMapper

Add products to cart → CartController → CartService → CartRepository

Checkout → OrderController → creates Order + OrderItems

Make payment → PaymentController → PaymentService → updates Order status

Optional review → ReviewController → saves user feedback on Product

All operations are secured via JWT, validated using DTOs, mapped via mappers, and persisted via repositories.

This design ensures:

Separation of concerns: Each package handles a single feature.

Scalability: Easy to add new features like coupons, wishlist, or shipping.

Testability: Services can be unit-tested independently.

Clean API: Controllers expose only DTOs, never internal entities.

